div.p: Kernel at 0xC0000000 virtual, loaded at 0x100000 physical

Color Legend: Header (.multiboot) - Must stay at physical address Code (.text) - Executable instructions Read-only data (.rodata) - Constants Data (.data) - Initialized globals BSS (.bss) - Uninitialized data (zeroed) Key Insight: AT() tells linker where to place section in the binary file, while virtual address is what code sees at runtime.
